CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 8 reads:"Frogs' Wives Entertain Glamorously at Loendi - Here They Are! - Frogs' wives and guests smile prettily for the cameraman during their charming coffee hour held at Loendi Club Monday night. Left photo, Frogs' wives all chat and sip while Mrs. Harry W. Washington, wife of the proxy, pours coffee.  Left to right are; Mrses. Reginald Dixon, James Haney, George Gould, William G. Nunn, Cornelius Jones and William Curtis...Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Mrs. Reginald Dixon, Mrs. James Haney, Mrs. George Gould, Mrs. William G. Nunn wearing print dress, Mrs. Cornelius Jones, and Mrs. William Curtis, standing around Mrs. Harry G .Washington pouring tea, in Loendi Club for FROGS wives coffee house
